div.p:
               When Mr A. B. Becker died in 1842 the pharmacy went as an inheritance to his nephew Mr E. G. Becker, a particularly able chemist;

It has not been possible to determine the date of Albert Becker's death. Notwithstanding M's statement here, it would seem that he was still alive in March 1843 (see A. Schütt to M, 10 March 1843), but he had almost certainly died by October 1844 when the privilege for the pharmacy was transferred to his nephew (Klatt (1988)). We are grateful for Dr Klatt's efforts to establish the date of death more precisely.
                and here I want to acknowledge late in life that both cared for the orphaned boy with almost fatherly affection. Yes, I still correspond today with the widow of Mr E. G. Becker, who died a few years ago in Berlin.
